@startuml
title Firestore vs SQL Database

left to right direction

card "Firestore (NoSQL)" as Firestore
[
- No complex relational queries
- Real-time data sync
- Flexible schema (document-based)
- Costs increase with reads/writes
- Limited advanced filtering/search
]

card "SQL Database" as SQL
[
- Strong relational data support
- No built-in real-time sync
- Structured schema (tables/rows)
- Costs tied to server setup/maintenance
- Supports complex queries & joins
]

Firestore <--> SQL : Comparison
@enduml
